HEADWORD: Piassava
<hw>Pi*as"sa*va</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pg.
<ets>piasaba</ets>.]</ety> <def>A fibrous product of two Brazilian palm
trees (<spn>Attalea funifera</spn> and <spn>Leopoldinia Piassaba</spn>),
-- used in making brooms, and for other purposes. Called also
<altname>pia⟦cced⟧aba</altname> and
<altname>piasaba</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Piaster</ent>⟦br⟧
